an><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">somebody has a house to sell are they going to be able to use that to get extra choice and a better care home?  Does that mean people like me will be put in one of those homes that are cheaper for the local authority, but are really badly run?  I have hear</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d about places like Orchard </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">V</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">iew and I am scared.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If I am being cared for at home and can’t afford to pay, will I be left with minimum hours, or nothing at all, as nobody can make a profit from me? </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(They had heard of a case in which an 84 year old had bee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n refused help from a private provider for being unprofitable).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We feel that care homes are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sometimes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">being set up by people with no background in care, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and the press has shown that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">staff in some homes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are badly trained and bullied</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">management</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Older peo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ple, even if they are paying a great deal of money, can end up abused and neglected.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Not all homes are like this, but too many are, and there is not always a choice as the good homes are filled up. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">They seem to want us to give up everything we have worke</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d for all our lives.  Well I am not paying a penny, I would rather die first. This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> reply</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, now becoming increasingly common,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was often added as a further response to the other comments we have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">summarised</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We feel that this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">runs the risk </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of leading</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to more</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> A&amp;E and hospital visits </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and admissions,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> thus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> putting a greater strain on the NHS. If people refuse to pay, care services may be lost, too.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">They are talking about taking our houses and valuables.  When will they do this?  Even if they don’t throw my husba</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nd out of our house</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> straight after I die</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, will they be coming for my personal possessions?  If I am the last survivor, will they be after even the rings I want to be buried in.  Will this override my will?  I want to give family stuff to my children…this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is like something out of Dickens.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Why should we pay all this money to live in cramped conditions, share a bathroom, and be fed overcooked bland food, followed by sitting in a circle around a TV?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Our </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">organization is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> concerned that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">current</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> proposals have th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e potential to lead to a two tier system, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">where</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">frail </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vulnerable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">older </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">people, without the means to pay, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">will be increasingly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">denied funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on the grounds they are not eligible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (even if they are very frail and vulnerable)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, by cash strapped Local Authoriti</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">es. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> also</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the fear of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman